\b\fs28 \cf2 jQuery can be used to select elements using a similar syntax to CSS \
\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0
\cf2 The format for selecting elements is: 
\b0\fs24 \
$("<element name, class, id, or XPath>") \
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\b\fs28 \cf2 \uc0\u8232 By calling $, we're just using a shorthand way of accessing the jQuery library's main function, that all others are descended from \u8232 \
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0
\cf2 Anonymous functions can be stored in variables: \
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\b0\fs24 \cf2 \
