\b\fs28 \cf2 Callbacks 
\b0\fs24 \
Anonymous functions are often used in 
\b callback
\b0 s \uc0\u8232 \
A 
\b callback 
\b0 is an anonymous function supplied to another \uc0\u8232 function to be run when that function is done running \u8232 \
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\b\fs28 \cf2 To use $(document).ready() and ensure the page is ready for your jQuery, you'll need to pass it an anonymous function (a callback) to execute when the document is ready \
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\b0\fs24 \cf2 $(document).ready(\
//Code that executes when the document is ready\
  function()\{\
    alert('The document is ready, sah!');\
  \}\
); \
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\b\fs28 \cf2 To show or hide an element on the page with jQuery, select it and call the show() or hide() function on your selection \
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\b0\fs24 \cf2 $("body").hide();\
$("body").show();\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\b\fs28 \cf2 To show or hide an element on the page using a fading animation, select it and call the fadeIn() or fadeOut() function on your selection 
\b0\fs24 \
$("#section-one").fadeOut();\
$("#section-one").fadeIn();\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\b\fs28 \cf2 You can give the fadeOut() and fadeIn() functions a time in milliseconds as an argument over which they should fade in and out 
\b0\fs24 \
$("#section-one").fadeOut(1000);\
//Fade out over 1 second\
$("#section-one").fadeIn(4000);\
//Fade in over 4 seconds\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\b\fs28 \cf2 Another way of hiding and showing items on the page is by using the slideUp() or slideDown() methods 
\b0\fs24 \
$("#section-one").slideUp(1000);\
//Fade out over 1 second\
$("#section-one").slideDown(4000);\
//Fade in over 4 seconds\
